        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix, press, bake, 11 to 13 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C fan. Line two baking trays with baking paper. Beat the {{peanut-butter}}, {{unsalted-butter}}, {{caster-sugar}}, and {{light-brown-sugar}} together until combined. Beat in the {{eggs}} and {{vanilla-extract}}. Fold in the {{plain-flour}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}} until a firm dough forms. Roll into balls of about 20 g each and place on the lined trays, spacing them 5 cm apart. Use a fork to press the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "cross-hatch",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9yhyou0000m8v49g43k2v6"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " pattern: press down once, then turn the fork 90° and press again. Bake for 11 to 13 minutes until the edges are set and the surface has lost its sheen. Cool on the tray for 10 minutes before moving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
